18:
"Menagerie of Oddities..." This is that
weird traveling show that came to
Palpebra.
21:
Here, read what they're exhibiting.
Flying frog, a cow with three udders,
and... TALKING DRAGONS.
27:
Yeeeah... Take that crap with a grain
of salt. All those freak shows are run
by cons.
30:
And, even if their claims were true, in
this world, there are a number of
dragons who speak the human
tongue. We do not know they have
Enith.
33:
I realize that, but this description of
how one of them looks... It fits Enith
to a T!
37:
Man, if she really is being shown off
as some kind of freak, I might lose
my mind.
40:
So you want us there to make sure
you don't do anything crazy.
61:
Next, feast your eyes on this rare
golden blobble!
63:
—It's so pretty...
—Eep! A monster!
—Hah! Bet he covered it with glitter!
74:
How do you expect me to chill?!
Look, I know logically speaking it's
not her, but I can't stop myself from
hoping!
77:
Now, for the moment you've all been
waiting for... The jewel of our show!
80:
TALKING DRAGONS! Rub your eyes,
folks, because this isn't a dream!
83: If THAT'S Enith, I'm head of the Guild...
86:
I do not think those dragons possess
much wisdom...
90:
What else did you expect from a
freak show?
101:
Huh? Oh yeah, I'm fine. Thanks for
asking...
103:
I'm relieved Enith wasn't captured,
but at the same time... I'm
disappointed I couldn't find her.
110: Now, who's ready to hear them talk?!
117:
Oy! Listen to me! We've practiced
this bit a million times!
119:
I've seen dogs better trained than
those dragons.
136:
This is exactly what happened at the
lake!
140: Move, Alk. Leave this to me.
161:
They WERE your family! They're
changed now—can't you see that?!
164: But why... Who did this to them?!
172:
I'm dumb and a coward... So I never
realized before but...
174:
We weren't angry at the dragons.
We were angry at what happened
to them.
176:
You loved those dragons. And so did
I!
184: Rover! Kitty! Gold Radish the Third!
191:
I never knew I had that power. Is it
because I'm a guardian?
193:
I hated having that role thrust on
me.
197:
So part of me was always scared
that everything happened because I
WANTED it to.
200: You're not that kind of person.
204:
Man, I'm so slow. Usually, it takes
Enith completely losing her mind
over something before I even BEGIN
to realize how I feel.
206:
It wasn't a curse OR retribution... I
think she WANTED to become a
dragon. To better express her rage
and grief.
210: She did look angry to me...
212:
But it also felt like she was
apologizing to you.
218:
Wait for me, Enith. That way, if
there's something you want to say
to me, you can say it to my face.
